<P>
</P>
<P>
The commission also recommended a raise for the President from $200,000 a year 
to $350,000, effective in 1993, since there is a constitutional ban against 
increasing the chief executive's pay during his term of office. 
</P>
<P>
 Source: Commission on Executive, Legislative and Judicial Salaries 
</P>
</TEXT>
