<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two suspects were arrested Wednesday night in connection with the Christmas Eve 
shooting death of a man in Stockton, Calif., after which the killers set the 
victim on fire in a 50-gallon oil drum filled with gasoline to dispose of the 
body, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Leroy Madsen, 33, and Michelle Stubblefield, 29, were arrested at 5 p.m. after 
detectives from the San Joaquin County Sheriff's Department and the San Diego 
Police Department served a search warrant at the hotel where they were staying 
at 13th and Market streets. The couple had been in San Diego about five days, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
The two were arrested in the death of Russell Wedge, 39. After Wedge was 
killed, police said he was wrapped in a blanket with ropes and carried a few 
days inside a car. The body was then stuffed head-first into a 50-gallon oil 
drum full of gas, placed inside a rented truck and set afire. 
</P>
<P>
The suspects were scheduled to be transferred to Stockton Thursday night to 
face charges there, police said. 
</P>
