<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: LA JOLLA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three workers at a construction site at UC San Diego were injured Thursday when 
they were struck by a hose that was spewing cement, said Paul Lowenberg, public 
information officer at the university. 
</P>
<P>
At 2 p.m., Pete Curto of La Mesa and John Yeakey, both 33, of Lakeside and 
Jaime Rocha, 37, of San Diego were working on the roof of the university's new 
molecular biology research building when workers lost control of a hose that 
was pumping cement. The hose continued to spray cement as it snaked 
uncontrollably, hitting the three men. 
</P>
<P>
The workers were taken to Scripps Hospital in La Jolla. Curto and Rocha were 
treated for back injuries, and Yeakey was treated for minor bruises, a hospital 
spokesman said. 
