BOYS' BASKETBALL; 
</P>
<P>
BURROUGHS PUTS SAN GABRIEL AWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROCKY PINHEIRO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Using its superior quickness and balanced scoring, Burroughs High rolled over 
San Gabriel, 77-57, Thursday night at Burroughs to remain undefeated in the 
Foothill League. 
</P>
<P>
In the early going it did not appear that the Indians would win so handily as 
the Matadors (3-15, 0-6 in league play) played stingy defense and trailed only 
40-35 at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
San Gabriel's Dean Smith closed the gap to 22-20 on a 4-foot shot with 2 
seconds left in the first quarter. It was not until late in the second quarter 
that Burroughs (14-5, 6-0) began to pull away. 
</P>
<P>
"We wanted to hold them down to our level and cause a lot of turnovers early," 
San Gabriel Coach Tim Knight said. "They are superior to us in every way, and 
unless we do this we'll get beat." 
</P>
<P>
Center Tom Clemens scored a team-high 18 points for Burroughs, which is ranked 
10th in the Valley by The Times. Guard Marnie Calderon added 16 points. ROCKY 
PINHEIRO 
</P>
</TEXT>
