<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Schurr 55, Burbank 50 -- Miguel Aristigui scored 9 of his 11 points in the last 
1:38 as Schurr came from behind to win the Foothill League game at Schurr. 
</P>
<P>
Aristigui made 2 free throws with 58 seconds to play to give Schurr (4-12, 4-2) 
a 51-50 lead, then added 4 more foul shots down the stretch. 
</P>
<P>
Aristigui gave Schurr a 49-48 lead with 1:22 remaining when he hit a 3-point 
shot, but Jim Cafferty of Burbank scored 12 seconds later to give the Bulldogs 
a 50-49 lead. 
</P>
<P>
Adam Tunison scored a game-high 21 points and Kahyeed Murray added 12 for 
Burbank (2-14, 1-5). 
</P>
<P>
Hart 71, Alhambra 63 (OT) -- Brett Wilson scored 7 of his 14 points in overtime 
to give Hart a Foothill League win at Alhambra. 
</P>
<P>
Wilson, who grabbed 10 rebounds in the game, hit 2 jump shots and 3 free throws 
in overtime. 
</P>
<P>
Alhambra's Pedro Diaz buried a 3-point shot with 4 seconds to play in 
regulation to tie the score, 59-59. 
</P>
<P>
Reserve forward Aaron Tanner made 5 of 5 field-goal attempts and finished with 
14 points for Hart (10-9, 4-2). 
</P>
<P>
Bel-Air Prep 59, Buckley 43 -- After battling for 3 quarters, Bel-Air Prep 
changed its defensive scheme from man-to-man into a triangle-and-two, forcing 6 
turnovers and holding Buckley to 3 points. 
</P>
<P>
Buckley's David Polushkian and Todd Steinman, who scored 14 each, were held to 
only 2 points in the final quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
