<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Vista, Calif.-based Southwest Bancorp announced that it has received a revised 
offer from Security Pacific Corp., Los Angeles, to acquire Southwest for $6 per 
share in Security Pacific common stock. Southwest's board has authorized 
negotiation of the terms of a definitive agreement. Southwest Bancorp comprises 
Southwest Bank and its wholly owned subsidiary, SW Mortgage Inc., a 
mortgage-banking concern. 
</P>
