<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nynex Corp.'s 1988 net income increased 3% to $1.32 billion on operating 
revenue of $12.7 billion, up 5%. Fourth-quarter earnings rose 6% to $342.2 
million on operating revenue of $3.2 billion, up 3% compared to the year-ago 
period. Officials of the White Plains, N.Y.-based telecommunications company 
said the acquisition of AGS Computers and an increase in the number of digital 
lines in service contributed to the results. 
</P>
