<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Prime-time cable TV programs became eligible for Emmy Awards last year, and now 
the Academy of Television Arts &amp; Sciences and the National Academy of 
Television Arts &amp; Sciences have opened Emmy competition to original daytime 
cable programming for the first time. Cable industry executives and personnel 
who work in daytime TV also may apply for membership in the two academies. The 
Daytime Emmy Awards will be presented June 29 in New York, with NBC carrying 
the ceremonies. ALEENE MacMINN 
