<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE TIMES' MIKE DOWNEY IS NAMED SPORTSWRITER OF YEAR IN CALIFORNIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Times columnist Mike Downey has been selected as sportswriter of the year in 
California by the National Sportscasters and Sportswriters Assn. 
</P>
<P>
Downey, who has been with The Times since 1985, previously was sportswriter of 
the year in Michigan in 1983 and 1984 while writing for the Detroit Free Press. 
</P>
<P>
Vin Scully, longtime voice of the Dodgers, was named California sportscaster of 
the year. 
</P>
<P>
Bob Costas of NBC was named national sportscaster of the year, and Frank Deford 
of Sports Illustrated was named national sportswriter of the year. 
</P>
<P>
Jim Murray of The Times, who has won the national award 14 times, was a 
finalist. 
</P>
