<TEXT>
<P>
Contrary to a neighbor's report, tenants -- not the landlord -- installed metal 
bars that rescuers said prevented them from saving Rachelle Jensen from a fire 
in her Stanton home Jan. 20, Laura Abbasi, wife of landlord Hossein Abbasi, 
said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
"We told them to remove them because they were not safe, but they wanted to 
keep them up," she said. 
</P>
<P>
For 7 years, the Jensens had rented an apartment in the four-unit building 
purchased a year and a half ago by Abbasi, she added. 
</P>
<P>
The Jensens could not be reached for comment. 
