<P>
2 YOUTHS HELD AFTER CHASE IN STOLEN CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two teen-agers in a stolen car led officers on a chase from Santa Ana to Los 
Angeles early Thursday before the car spun out of control on Century Boulevard 
and the pair surrendered, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
A Santa Ana police office patrolling in the 2000 block of Southwood Street at 
about 2:45 a.m. saw two youths in a 1987 Hyundai that had been reported stolen 
from Irvine earlier in the evening, Santa Ana police spokeswoman Maureen Thomas 
said. The youths ignored the officer's attempt to stop them, drove west on 
Warner Avenue and headed north on the San Diego Freeway, Thomas added. 
</P>
<P>
After a high-speed, 30-minute chase, the car spun out of control on Century 
Boulevard after leaving the freeway. No one was injured, and the car was not 
damaged. The youths, ages 15 and 16 and both from Santa Ana, were arrested on 
suspicion of possession of stolen property, evading arrest and reckless 
driving. 
</P>
