<P>
OCEAN VIEW'S NORMAN PICKS NOTRE DAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Todd Norman, an all-Sunset League linebacker the past 2 seasons at Ocean View 
High School, has made a oral commitment to attend Notre Dame in the fall, 
Norman said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Norman, 6 feet 6 inches and 245 pounds, led Ocean View in tackles with 95 last 
season and was a second-team Times' all-county selection. He also played 
offensive guard but was being recruiting as a linebacker. Norman also had 
considered USC and UCLA. 
</P>
<P>
Norman also is a standout on the basketball team. He is averaging 21.4 points 
and 11 rebounds for the Oilers (13-6 overall, 3-2 in league play). 
</P>
<P>
Norman had taken trips to national champion Notre Dame and to USC the last 2 
weekends. He was planning to go to visit UCLA this weekend, but canceled the 
trip after picking Notre Dame. 
</P>
<P>
"My visit was what did it," Norman said. "It's a beautiful campus and area, and 
they have the football tradition going again. I'm ready to try something new. 
I'm leaving a nice area to go to a nice area." STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
