<P>
SHRIVER SON PULLS OUT OF ORIOLE DEAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BALTIMORE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Robert S. Shriver III has withdrawn from a group of four investors who agreed 
to purchase the Baltimore Orioles last year for $70 million, Orioles president 
Larry Lucchino said. 
</P>
<P>
Shriver -- called "the architect of the sale" by his father, R. Sargent 
Shriver, also an investor -- left the group a couple of weeks ago to 
concentrate on other business interests, Lucchino said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
The Orioles sale to the elder Shriver, Lucchino and New York financier Eli S. 
Jacobs cannot become official until approved by three-fourths of the 14 
American League owners and a majority of the 12 National League owners. Jacobs 
is the majority investor in the group. 
